About The Hindley Street Country Club (HSCC) is an Australian group founded in 2017 by arranger and producer Constantine Delo. The band specializes in innovative cover arrangements that have achieved massive viral success through social media.
Starting as a group of Adelaide musicians recording re-arranged covers, HSCC uploads fresh videos weekly. What sets them apart is their creative approach to arranging classic funk, soul, and R&amp;B tracks with unique instrumental combinations and energetic performances. The formula has resonated globally, earning them over 540 million YouTube views, 940,000+ YouTube subscribers, and more than a billion views across all social media platforms.
Their viral success has transformed them from local musicians into touring artists who perform worldwide while maintaining their commitment to weekly YouTube releases every Friday. Each video showcases their talented ensemble performing elaborate arrangements that reimagine beloved songs from various genres.
YouTube (HSCC) They have covered a huge amount of songs, Here are just a few of my favourites;
